    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Front Cover and Related Components -
        Inspection - Checking Camshaft Gear Backlash
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Checking Camshaft Gear Backlash</title>
        <figure id="f2650632" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh06/h06050.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Checking camshaft gear backlash</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial indicator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft gear</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Pressure exerted by the valve train must be relieved before doing the following procedure.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clamp a dial indicator on the front cover or the cylinder head if the dial indicator stand
                is magnetic
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the tip of the dial indicator as tangent as possible to a gear tooth and zero dial
                indicator.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a screwdriver between the upper idler gear and the lower idler gear to keep the upper
                idler gear from rotating.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the camshaft gear back and forth. Record reading on the dial indicator face. If the
                backlash exceeds specifications, replace camshaft gear.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
